## This is my test project for my upcoming bachelor's thesis

The project is to setup a virtual GNS3 network connected to my local network.

This approach allows me to use Ansbile to push new configurations on the network devices.

# The topology
![Toplogy](Topology.png)

# Basic workflow
For this project I will be using GNS3 to create a virtual network lab. I will bridge the devices to my home network. Raspberry Pi will be running Ansible and checking GitHub for new commits to determine configuration changes. 
After this an automated CI/CD pipeline will run which triggers pyATS to perform tests to determine if the configurations are valid. It will then either apply or reject the changes.

# Device configurations
We only need the following initial configurations on the network devices
- IP address
- SSH
